Thanks — you were right, parent_commits min_length=1 is enforced. Updated the plan:

- Planner host gains --base-commit-sha HEX (required). Its scripted plan_fn emits proposals with parent_commits=(base_commit_sha,).
- Implementer reads proposal.parent_commits[0] as the parent for its new commit (no separate flag — it honors what the proposal carries).
- Test harness seeds the bare repo with an empty initial commit via a new _common seed_bare_repo(path) helper; passes the resulting SHA to the planner as --base-commit-sha.
- Spec reachability story (§1.4 + §2) restored to non-trivial: trial.parent_commits contains the base SHA, and the implementer's new commit descends from it.

Please review the updated plan at /Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-8b-service-extraction.md.
