 succeeded in 0ms:
   690	   plan file, `07-wire-protocol.md` addendum, each service README,
   691	   and AGENTS.md + CLAUDE.md + roadmap updates.
   692	6. Manual: start task-store-server on a real port, curl
   693	   `GET /v0/experiments/exp-1/events` without an `Authorization`
   694	   header — returns 401 problem+json with `type:
   695	   eden://reference-error/unauthorized`. Same request with
   696	   `Authorization: Bearer <token>` returns 200 empty events.
   697	7. Manual: kill the task-store-server with `kill -TERM` and confirm
   698	   clean exit (no tracebacks, SQLite file well-formed).
   699	
   700	## Out of scope for 8b
   701	
   702	(Already listed in Non-goals; restated here as the commit guardrail.)
   703	
   704	- Removing in-process dispatch paths (Phase 8c).
   705	- SSE / WebSocket push.
   706	- Real auth (per-worker identities, rotation, expiry, transport
   707	  security). Milestone 3.
   708	- Artifact store transport (Phase 10).
   709	- UI (Phase 9).
   710	- Compose packaging (Phase 10).
   711	- `healthz` endpoint.
   712	- Multi-experiment (Phase 12).
   713	- Worker claim-expiry / health-policy reclaim (spec-supported but
   714	  not exercised by the E2E harness; it's not 8b's job to harden the
   715	  reclaim path).
   716	
   717	## Known risks
   718	
   719	- **Subprocess-based integration tests are easy to write wrong.** The
   720	  E2E spec above is explicit about: ephemeral ports announced on
   721	  stdout; stderr capture on failure; bounded timeouts at every wait
   722	  point; SIGKILL fallback on SIGTERM timeout; tempdir teardown on
   723	  every exit path. Missing any of these yields a test that hangs CI
   724	  or produces unrunnable "red for unknown reason" failures. These
   725	  are codified in the test, not left to diligence.
   726	- **Auth in the non-normative namespace is a cross-concern edit.**
   727	  `eden_wire.errors._TYPE_BY_EXC` currently maps only `StorageError`
   728	  subclasses to `eden://error/…`. The new `Unauthorized` exception
   729	  lives outside that map because (a) it's not a `StorageError`, and
   730	  (b) it's reference-only. Keep the two tables clearly separated so
   731	  no future refactor accidentally leaks a reference-only type into
   732	  the normative vocabulary.
   733	- **Workers don't self-terminate.** Anything that boots a worker
   734	  (test harness, future deployment) is responsible for killing it.
   735	  SIGTERM triggers a clean exit within one poll interval; SIGKILL
   736	  is the fallback after 10 seconds. Documented in each service's
   737	  README.
   738	- **Shared-token auth has no transport security.** The server is
   739	  loopback-only in tests and documented as such. A real deployment
   740	  of shared-token auth over a non-TLS link leaks the token. Auth
   741	  scaffolding has a big caveat in its README pointing at Milestone
   742	  3.
   743	- **Windows signal handling.** `signal.SIGTERM` on Windows is
   744	  missing; uvicorn's shutdown path uses `SIGBREAK` / SIGINT. The
   745	  E2E test is `pytest.mark.skipif(sys.platform == "win32", …)`.
   746	  Non-test code paths also work on Windows (uvicorn handles it),
   747	  just not exercised in CI.
   748	- **Quiescence counter ≥ 2.** If
   749	  `--max-quiescent-iterations` is 1, the orchestrator can exit
   750	  while a worker is mid-submit (the orchestrator reads tasks, sees
   751	  nothing pending, exits; the worker's submit lands a moment
   752	  later, orphaned). Default of 3 plus a poll interval of 0.1s
   753	  means we wait ~0.2s of no-progress, which empirically covers
   754	  scripted-worker latency with a wide margin. Documented as a
   755	  tunable.
   756	- **Ephemeral port assignment race.** We bind `--port 0`, read the
   757	  port from stdout, then launch other processes pointing at it.
   758	  Between `listen()` and the port being printed there's a
   759	  flush-timing window where the harness might read an empty line;
   760	  the harness must `readline()` in a loop until it gets the
   761	  `EDEN_TASK_STORE_LISTENING` prefix. Harness code handles this.
   762	- **`--plan-tasks N` (integer) vs explicit list.** The integer form
   763	  is the common case; the explicit-list form exists so tests can
   764	  pin deterministic IDs that assertions can reference.
   765	- **Scripted `plan_fn` / `implement_fn` / `evaluate_fn` now live in
   766	  shared code.** Tests that used to inject their own fn still can,
   767	  by importing and parameterizing — no lock-in. The shared
   768	  defaults are the deterministic "3 trials, all succeed" shape
   769	  that the Phase 5 / 7b E2E uses.
   770	
   771	## Execution order
   772	
   773	This is execution-only; no scope decisions are deferred to here.
   774	
   775	1. Spec addendum: append §8 "Reference-only extensions" to
   776	   [`spec/v0/07-wire-protocol.md`](../../spec/v0/07-wire-protocol.md).
   777	   Run `python3 scripts/spec-xref-check.py` to confirm no broken
   778	   xrefs. Lint with markdownlint.
   779	2. Refactor `eden-dispatch.driver`: extract
   780	   `_run_orchestrator_iteration` (private) and keep
   781	   `run_experiment` calling it. Add
   782	   `reference/packages/eden-dispatch/tests/test_orchestrator_iteration.py`.
   783	3. Extend `eden-wire.server.make_app` with the `shared_token`
   784	   kwarg + middleware. Extend `eden-wire.client.StoreClient` with
   785	   `token` kwarg. Add `Unauthorized` exception + reference-only
   786	   entry to `eden_wire.errors`. Add
   787	   `reference/packages/eden-wire/tests/test_auth.py` covering
   788	   server middleware + client header + error round-trip.
   789	4. Land `reference/services/_common/` with logging, signal
   790	   handling, readiness probe, arg parsing, and the scripted
   791	   `plan_fn`/`implement_fn`/`evaluate_fn` extraction.
   792	5. Land `reference/services/task-store-server/` with its tests
   793	   (unit `test_app.py`).
   794	6. Land `reference/services/orchestrator/` with its unit
   795	   tests but not the E2E yet.
   796	7. Land `reference/services/planner/`, `implementer/`,
   797	   `evaluator/` with their host unit tests.
   798	8. Land the E2E test
   799	   `reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_e2e.py`.
   800	   Run locally — it is the acceptance gate for 8b. Capture stderr
   801	   on failure from the beginning; do not add that feature as a
   802	   "v2" polish.
   803	9. Update `reference/README.md`: mark the five service directories
   804	   as Phase 8b-complete.
   805	10. Update `AGENTS.md` "Current phase" and the Commands table
   806	    (python module invocation hints for the new services).
   807	11. Update `docs/roadmap.md` Phase 8 section: mark 8b complete.
   808	12. Run the full verification list above.
   809	13. `/codex-review references/implementation.md` on the branch.
   810	14. Codify findings; commit; PR.
   811	
   812	## Review gate
   813	
   814	Before handing to `/codex-review`:
   815	
   816	- The plan answers, for each of the five design decisions, what the
   817	  chosen option is and why the alternatives were rejected:
   818	  - **Quiescence by iteration counter vs by event subscription.**
   819	    Counter chosen because (a) it matches how `run_experiment`
   820	    already detects quiescence and (b) doesn't require the worker
   821	    hosts to distinguish "I'm idle" from "I exited" on the
   822	    subscriber end.
   823	  - **Workers poll tasks vs subscribe to events.** Polling chosen
   824	    for 8b because teardown (kill at any moment) is trivial and
   825	    because the poll interval is a single tunable. Event-subscribe
   826	    remains a future optimization.
   827	  - **Shared-token in normative vocabulary vs reference-only
   828	    namespace.** Reference-only chosen because the spec chapter
   829	    07 explicitly defers auth to Milestone 3 and committing to a
   830	    shape now would force rework then.
   831	  - **Common scaffolding extracted vs inlined per service.**
   832	    Extracted because three divergent CLIs are the predictable
   833	    failure mode and because the extraction is small (< 200 LOC).
   834	  - **Service directories — reuse stubs vs new names.** Reuse the
   835	    four existing Phase 0 stubs (`planner/`, `implementer/`,
   836	    `evaluator/`, `orchestrator/`) — they are the roadmap's blessed
   837	    names and [`reference/README.md`](../../reference/README.md)
   838	    already documents them. Add one new directory
   839	    (`task-store-server/`) for the process that holds the store;
   840	    there is no stub because Phase 0 didn't anticipate splitting

